uins, reanimation, ghosts and journeys to the underworld.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAllusions in literature. 0aUncanny, The (Psychoanalysis), in literature. 4aGothic 2017. 4aShakespeare 2018. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aGreek tragedy.  aLatin epic.  aShakespeare.  aVictorian novel.  aallusion.  afiction.  afilm.  aghosts.  apoetry.  auncanny.1 aBrown, Sarah Annes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612541540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526125415423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526125415/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles